relationships.description: Political opponents in the US presidential election

analysis.purpose: To report on social media sentiment analysis and election predictions based on Twitter data
analysis.significance: Provides quantitative analysis of public sentiment during the 2016 US presidential election campaign period

blackmail_indicators.description: No indicators of blackmail or coercion present in this analytical report

illegal_activity.description: No illegal activity discussed or evidenced in this analytical report

public_knowledge.context: This appears to be election analysis data from the 2016 US presidential election between Donald Trump and Hillary Clinton, which was widely covered by media

analysis.summary: This report analyzes Twitter sentiment data from November 2016 showing Donald Trump with 45.68% negative sentiment vs Hillary Clinton's 58.77% negative sentiment, with Trump predicted to have 55% chance of winning based on state-by-state analysis.
